Q&A:

Q: What size of the screen to choose?
A: Screen size 640x360. I want pixel art but to to squary

Q: What size for the ships to choose?
A: 32x32 with posibility to add some interesting details and get not to pixelated look on and not to boring as 16x16 an

Q: What is the maximun number of ships I plan to put on the screen (with and height)
A: Width: 16 units; Height: 9 units

Q: Tools. What Kind of tools I need: to create or add-ons to use from store

Q: Do I need particles effect to make rocket explosion?
A: Lets train art skils and do animation.

Q: Do I need particles effect to make ship(player, enemy) explosion?
A: Lets train art skils and do animation.

Q: Do I need particles effect for blaster got the enemy?
A: Lets train art skils and do animation.

Q: Do I need particles effect for raycast got enemy?
A: Lets train art skils and make explosion as animation.

Q: Do I need a unit testing here? I saw eventualy an add-on that makes unit tests possible
A: Looks like GUT is the answer (https://github.com/bitwes/Gut) but may be WAT also (https://github.com/CodeDarigan/WAT/)

Q: Techniques to test levels??

Q: Do I need sound effects for ship movement?
A: Lets say no as ther will be background music and laser shots fjrom player 1 and player 2 and enemies and explosions etc.

Q: How to make music an sfx?
A: list
    - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GJRMmJnpknY

